This branch is made on top of the neighbour_client_server branch
Rebase your work on top of this before pushing.
this can be done using

git fetch --all
If you have uncommitted work: git stash
git rebase neighbour_client_server
And, if you used stash: git stash pop
now push your changes.

How I've built and run the database during development

docker build -t interchanges_test .
docker run -it -e POSTGRES_USER=federation -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=federation -e POSTGRES_DB=federation -p 7070:5432 --name interchange_container interchanges_test

docker exec -it interchange_container bash
psql -U federation -d federation
insert into interchanges (ixn_id, interchange_status, name, domain_name, control_channel_port) values (0,'FEDERATED','myIxn','kyrre.priv.no','4443');
